		"description": "<p>At 2nd level, your training allows you to harness your mental energy into a supernatural state of focus. Some cultures refer to this energy as ax&eacute;, prana, pneuma, or ki. Your access to this energy is represented by your exertion pool. You can spend exertion points to fuel various focus features.</p>\n<p>You start knowing three such features: Flurry of Blows, Long Step, and Patient Defense. You learn more focus features as you gain levels in this class.</p>\n<p>Some of your focus features require your target to make a saving throw to resist the feature&rsquo;s effects. The saving throw DC is calculated as follows:</p>\n<p><strong>Focus save DC</strong> = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier</p>",
